<tableCitation id="F91E0373FF8245787CC9FD8F0AD094F3" box="[402,418,618,642]" captionStart="TABLE 9" captionStartId="52.[151,234,1198,1221]" captionText="TABLE 9. Summary statistics for taxa recognised by this study." pageId="46" pageNumber="47">9</tableCitation>
). Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="739C4D4BFF8245787F74FD8E09D794F2" authorityName="Taylor &amp; Lavrenchenko &amp; Carleton &amp; Verheyen &amp; Bennett &amp; Oosthuizen &amp; Maree" authorityYear="2011" box="[559,677,619,643]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Otomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yaldeni">
<emphasis id="86E8EADAFF8245787F74FD8E09D794F2" box="[559,677,619,643]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">O. yaldeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but considerably larger externally (HB mean 
<quantity id="73649B2DFF82457879F7FD8F0E7A94F3" box="[1196,1288,618,642]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.55" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="155.0">155 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName id="739C4D4BFF8245787875FD8E0EE794F3" authorityName="Taylor &amp; Lavrenchenko &amp; Carleton &amp; Verheyen &amp; Bennett &amp; Oosthuizen &amp; Maree" authorityYear="2011" box="[1326,1429,619,642]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Otomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simiensis">
<emphasis id="86E8EADAFF8245787875FD8E0EE794F3" box="[1326,1429,619,642]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">simiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, cf. 
<quantity id="73649B2DFF8245787DE1FD6B0A7394D7" box="[186,257,654,678]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6322" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="in" value="143.0">143 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="739C4D4BFF8245787C5CFD6B0A2B94D7" authorityName="Taylor &amp; Lavrenchenko &amp; Carleton &amp; Verheyen &amp; Bennett &amp; Oosthuizen &amp; Maree" authorityYear="2011" box="[263,345,654,678]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Otomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yaldeni">
<emphasis id="86E8EADAFF8245787C5CFD6B0A2B94D7" box="[263,345,654,678]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">yaldeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; tail means 
<quantity id="73649B2DFF8245787CBBFD6B095F94D7" box="[480,557,654,678]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.3" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="83.0">83 mm</quantity>
and 
<quantity id="73649B2DFF8245787F38FD6B09C394D7" box="[611,689,654,678]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.2" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="72.0">72 mm</quantity>
respectively); skull having a narrower interorbital region, less pronounced supraorbital ridges, relatively longer nasal bones, and braincase with flatter dorsal profile (
<figureCitation id="2CA72A4DFF82457879A3FD570E3E94BB" box="[1272,1356,690,714]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="48.[151,249,1971,1994]" captionTargetBox="[196,1367,183,1936]" captionTargetId="figure-35@48.[196,1384,177,1946]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURE 17(a–c). Photographs comparing dorsal, ventral and lateral views of the skulls of holotype of Otomys yaldeni (ZMMU 162594)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280622" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280622/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
); karyotype distinctive (2N=54, NF=56).
</paragraph>
